{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐπιδημ-έω</b>, <br /> <b>to be at home, live at home</b>, opposed to ἀποδημέω, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.136, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Tht.” 173e, etc.; παρόντες καὶ ἐπιδημοῦντες 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 6.46; ἐ. τρία ἔη Andocides Orator [{5-6th c.BC}] 1.132 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. Ἀθήνησι <b>stay at</b> <b>home</b> at Athens, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 35.16; so ἐν αὐτῇ (i.e. τῇ πόλει) ἐ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cri.” 52b; opposed to στρατεύομαι, 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 9.3. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3>. of diseases, <b>to be prevalent, epidemic</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Prog..” 25. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2>. <b>come home</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Mem.” 2.8.1; ἐνθάδε ἐ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Smp.” 172c; εἰ νῦν ἐξ ἀγροῦ ἐνθάδ᾽ ἐπιδημεῖ Menander Comicus [{4-3rd c.BC}] “Γεωργός” 19 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2>. of foreigners, <b>come to stay in a city, reside in</b> a place, οἱ -οῦντες ἐν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Λακεδαίμονι ξένοι Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Memorabilia” 1.2.61 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. εἰς Μέγαρα <b>come</b> to Megara <b>to</b> <b>stay</b> there, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 59.37, compare 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 2.154; ἐκ Κλαζομενῶν Plato Philosophus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Parmenides” 126b \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. τοῖς μυστηρίοις <b>to be present at, attend</b> them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.176; τοὺς ἐπιδημήσαντας ἅπαντας τῶν Ἑλλήνων\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] all <b>who were present</b>[at the festival], [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 217; Φοίβου ἐπιδημήσαντος 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hymnus in Apollinem” 13 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]: laterc. <i>dative</i>,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ταῖς Σάρδεσιν Philostratus Sophista [{2-3rd c.AD}] “Vitae Sophistarum” 1.22.4; also ἐν Μέμφει “UPZ” 42i4 (2nd c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3>. <i>absolutely</i>,<b>stay in a</b> <b>place, be in town</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ὅσοι ξένοι ἐπιδημοῦσιν 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 12.35, compare “Inscription Prien.” 108.286 (2nd c.BC), NT.Acts.17.21; Πρωταγόρας ἐπιδεδήμηκε; 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Prt.” 309d: _metaphorically_, ἐ. θίασος Μουσῶν Aristophanes Comicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Thesmophoriazusae” 40 \">NT+6th c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3>. ἐ. τινί <b>visit</b> a person, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PLond.” 2.416.5 (4th c.AD). \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1927","accentedUnicode":"ἐπιδημέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1218","matchingForm":"δῆμος","stepTransliteration":"dēmos","gloss":"people","_zh_tw_Gloss":"百姓","_es_Gloss":"gente ","_zh_Gloss":"百姓"},{"strongNumber":"G1909","matchingForm":"ἐπί","stepTransliteration":"epi","gloss":"upon/to/against","_zh_tw_Gloss":"在","_es_Gloss":"sobre/a/contra ","_zh_Gloss":"在"},{"strongNumber":"G3927","matchingForm":"παρεπίδημος","stepTransliteration":"parepidēmos","gloss":"stranger","_zh_tw_Gloss":"寄居","_es_Gloss":"forastero","_zh_Gloss":"寄居"}],"shortDef":"to live asbe a visitor, foreigner","mediumDef":"to live asbe a visitor, foreigner <br /><b>to dwell among a people; to be at home among one's own people;</b>, and in NT <b>to sojourn as a stranger among another people,</b> <ref='Act.2.10'>Acts 2:10;</ref> 17:21*","stepGloss":"to sojourn","stepTransliteration":"epidēmeō","count":2,"_es_Definition":"visitar ; vivir en un lugar","_zh_tw_Definition":"客居 (徒 2:10, 17:21)","_zh_Definition":"客居 (徒 2:10, 17:21)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"ở nhà; để ở, cư trú (tạm thời, ở một thành phố nước ngoài). ἐπί (G1